        "monster_family": {
          "name": "Courtier",
          "subtype": "monster_family",
          "subtypes": [
            {
              "changes": [
                {
                  "abilities": [
                    {
                      "ability_type": "ability",
                      "name": "Ball",
                      "subtype": "ability",
                      "text": ": a formal dance party that often includes a banquet",
                      "type": "stat_block_section"
                    }
                  ],
                  "change_category": "abilities",
                  "effects": [
                    {
                      "operation": "add_items",
                      "source": "$.monster_family.subtypes[*].changes[*].abilities",
                      "target": "$.defense.automatic_abilities"
                    }
                  ],
                  "subtype": "change",
                  "text": "Know Your Social Events",
                  "type": "stat_block_section"
                }
              ],
              "name": "Know Your Social Events",
              "subtype": "monster_family",
              "text": "* \n* **Banquet**: an elaborate formal meal for a large number of people\n* **Debutante Ball**: a ball where upper-class youths formally enter society as adults\n* **Gala**: a social occasion with special entertainment or performances\n* **Hunt**: a formal hunting competition among the nobility and royals of court\n* **Masque**: a dramatic performance with singing, dancing, pantomime, and dialogue",
              "type": "stat_block_section"
            }
          ],
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        "name": "Courtier",
        "sections": [
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "Aiuvarin translator",
                "aonid": 3630,
                "game-obj": "NPCs",
                "name": "Aiuvarin translator",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Crossover Ancestry NPCs",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 12",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 12",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 12,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Several of the NPCs elsewhere in NPC Core can fit well in this group: Aiuvarin translator (level 0)",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "name": "Intriguing Plots",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 12",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 12",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 12,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "The royal court is filled with intrigue! Here are some examples of who might be scheming. \n* The monarch's spouse or children\n* The royal pet (a druid in disguise)\n* The grand vizier\n* Visiting ambassadors or nobles\n* Palace champion\n* Palace doctor\n* Kitchen staff\n* Court jester",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "name": "Social Warfare",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 12",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 12",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 12,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Though courtiers might have guards and servants at their command, their most potent forces are their connections outside of court and the will of the common people. A noble might have financial control of the entertainment district, but a popular courtesan moving their patronage will take their admirers with them. An envoy who endears themselves to commoners by having their spies expose corrupt officials can provoke public outrage when a rival attempts to have them replaced.",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "link": {
              "alt": "NPC Core pg. 12",
              "aonid": 236,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "NPC Core pg. 12",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "NPC Core",
            "page": 12,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "The denizens of a noble court are the most powerful people in a civilization, primed with wealth, station, and authority above the common people.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
